15class RootVisitor;
16struct ScriptDetails;

18// The compilation cache consists of several sub-caches: one each for evals and
19// scripts, which use this class as a base class, and a separate generational
20// sub-cache for RegExps. Since the same source code string has different
21// compiled code for scripts and evals, we use separate sub-caches for different
22// compilation modes, to avoid retrieving the wrong result.
23class CompilationCacheEvalOrScript {
24 public:
25 explicit CompilationCacheEvalOrScript(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {}
26
27 // Allocates the table if it didn't yet exist.
28 Handle<CompilationCacheTable> GetTable();
29
30 // GC support.
31 void Iterate(RootVisitor* v);
32
33 // Clears this sub-cache evicting all its content.
34 void Clear();
35
36 // Removes given shared function info from sub-cache.
37 void Remove(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info);
38
39 protected:
40 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
41
42 Isolate* const isolate_;
43 Tagged<Object> table_;
44
45 DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(CompilationCacheEvalOrScript);
46};
47
48// Sub-cache for scripts.
49class CompilationCacheScript : public CompilationCacheEvalOrScript {
50 public:
51 explicit CompilationCacheScript(Isolate* isolate)
52 : CompilationCacheEvalOrScript(isolate) {}
53
54 using LookupResult = CompilationCacheScriptLookupResult;
55 LookupResult Lookup(Handle<String> source,
56 const ScriptDetails& script_details);
57
58 void Put(Handle<String> source, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info);
59
60 void Age();
61
62 private:
63 DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(CompilationCacheScript);
64};
65
66// Sub-cache for eval scripts. Two caches for eval are used. One for eval calls
67// in native contexts and one for eval calls in other contexts. The cache
68// considers the following pieces of information when checking for matching
69// entries:
70// 1. The source string.
71// 2. The shared function info of the calling function.
72// 3. Whether the source should be compiled as strict code or as sloppy code.
73// Note: Currently there are clients of CompileEval that always compile
74// sloppy code even if the calling function is a strict mode function.
75// More specifically these are the CompileString, DebugEvaluate and
76// DebugEvaluateGlobal runtime functions.
77// 4. The start position of the calling scope.
78class CompilationCacheEval : public CompilationCacheEvalOrScript {
79 public:
80 explicit CompilationCacheEval(Isolate* isolate)
81 : CompilationCacheEvalOrScript(isolate) {}
82
83 InfoCellPair Lookup(Handle<String> source,
84 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info,
85 Handle<Context> native_context,
86 LanguageMode language_mode, int position);
87
88 void Put(Handle<String> source, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info,
89 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info,
90 Handle<Context> native_context, Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell,
91 int position);
92
93 void Age();
94
95 private:
96 DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(CompilationCacheEval);
97};
98
99// Sub-cache for regular expressions.
100class CompilationCacheRegExp {
101 public:
102 CompilationCacheRegExp(Isolate* isolate) : isolate_(isolate) {}
103
104 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Lookup(Handle<String> source, JSRegExp::Flags flags);
105
106 void Put(Handle<String> source, JSRegExp::Flags flags,
107 Handle<FixedArray> data);
108
109 // The number of generations for the RegExp sub cache.
110 static const int kGenerations = 2;
111
112 // Gets the compilation cache tables for a specific generation. Allocates the
113 // table if it does not yet exist.
114 Handle<CompilationCacheTable> GetTable(int generation);
115
116 // Ages the sub-cache by evicting the oldest generation and creating a new
117 // young generation.
118 void Age();
119
120 // GC support.
121 void Iterate(RootVisitor* v);
122
123 // Clears this sub-cache evicting all its content.
124 void Clear();
125
126 private:
127 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
128
129 Isolate* const isolate_;
130 Tagged<Object> tables_[kGenerations]; // One for each generation.
131
132 DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(CompilationCacheRegExp);
133};
134
135// The compilation cache keeps shared function infos for compiled
136// scripts and evals. The shared function infos are looked up using
137// the source string as the key. For regular expressions the
138// compilation data is cached.
139class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CompilationCache {
140 public:
141 CompilationCache(const CompilationCache&) = delete;
142 CompilationCache& operator=(const CompilationCache&) = delete;
143
144 // Finds the Script and root SharedFunctionInfo for a script source string.
145 // Returns empty handles if the cache doesn't contain a script for the given
146 // source string with the right origin.
147 CompilationCacheScript::LookupResult LookupScript(
148 Handle<String> source, const ScriptDetails& script_details,
149 LanguageMode language_mode);
150
151 // Finds the shared function info for a source string for eval in a
152 // given context. Returns an empty handle if the cache doesn't
153 // contain a script for the given source string.
154 InfoCellPair LookupEval(Handle<String> source,
155 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info,
156 Handle<Context> context, LanguageMode language_mode,
157 int position);
158
159 // Returns the regexp data associated with the given regexp if it
160 // is in cache, otherwise an empty handle.
161 MaybeHandle<FixedArray> LookupRegExp(Handle<String> source,
162 JSRegExp::Flags flags);
163
164 // Associate the (source, kind) pair to the shared function
165 // info. This may overwrite an existing mapping.
166 void PutScript(Handle<String> source, LanguageMode language_mode,
167 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info);
168
169 // Associate the (source, context->closure()->shared(), kind) triple
170 // with the shared function info. This may overwrite an existing mapping.
171 void PutEval(Handle<String> source, Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> outer_info,
172 Handle<Context> context,
173 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info,
174 Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell, int position);
175
176 // Associate the (source, flags) pair to the given regexp data.
177 // This may overwrite an existing mapping.
178 void PutRegExp(Handle<String> source, JSRegExp::Flags flags,
179 Handle<FixedArray> data);
180
181 // Clear the cache - also used to initialize the cache at startup.
182 void Clear();
183
184 // Remove given shared function info from all caches.
185 void Remove(Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> function_info);
186
187 // GC support.
188 void Iterate(RootVisitor* v);
189
190 // Notify the cache that a mark-sweep garbage collection is about to
191 // take place. This is used to retire entries from the cache to
192 // avoid keeping them alive too long without using them.
193 void MarkCompactPrologue();
194
195 // Enable/disable compilation cache. Used by debugger to disable compilation
196 // cache during debugging so that eval and new scripts are always compiled.
197 // TODO(bmeurer, chromium:992277): The RegExp cache cannot be enabled and/or
198 // disabled, since it doesn't affect debugging. However ideally the other
199 // caches should also be always on, even in the presence of the debugger,
200 // but at this point there are too many unclear invariants, and so I decided
201 // to just fix the pressing performance problem for RegExp individually first.
202 void EnableScriptAndEval();
203 void DisableScriptAndEval();
204
205 private:
206 explicit CompilationCache(Isolate* isolate);
207 ~CompilationCache() = default;
208
209 base::HashMap* EagerOptimizingSet();
210
211 bool IsEnabledScriptAndEval() const {
212 return v8_flags.compilation_cache && enabled_script_and_eval_;
213 }
214 bool IsEnabledScript(LanguageMode language_mode) {
215 // Tests can change v8_flags.use_strict at runtime. The compilation cache
216 // only contains scripts which were compiled with the default language mode.
217 return IsEnabledScriptAndEval() && language_mode == LanguageMode::kSloppy;
218 }
219
220 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
221
222 Isolate* isolate_;
223
224 CompilationCacheScript script_;
225 CompilationCacheEval eval_global_;
226 CompilationCacheEval eval_contextual_;
227 CompilationCacheRegExp reg_exp_;
228
229 // Current enable state of the compilation cache for scripts and eval.
230 bool enabled_script_and_eval_;
231
232 friend class Isolate;
233};
234
235} // namespace internal
236} // namespace v8
